docs.abstract: Amazon has tried out numerous experiments in its hometown, cementing the city’s reputation as a hub for retail innovation.

docs.lead_paragraph: How do behemoth technology companies test out new concepts? If you are Amazon, you use your hometown as a living lab.

docs.abstract: Investors have long been generous with Amazon. But lower-than-expected quarterly revenue growth dropped the company’s share price more than 4 percent.
docs.snippet: Investors have long been generous with Amazon. But lower-than-expected quarterly revenue growth dropped the company’s share price more than 4 percent.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Amazon showed the kind of growth over the holidays that most big companies would die for, as it continued to suck away sales from crumbling bricks-and-mortar retailers. But it was not enough.

docs.abstract: Consumers have felt liberated from traditional packages of media, music and retail services, but what they’ve really done is trade one bundle for another.
docs.snippet: Consumers have felt liberated from traditional packages of media, music and retail services, but what they’ve really done is trade one bundle for another.
docs.lead_paragraph: The internet promised to be the great unbundler. The evisceration of distribution costs would free consumers from paying for cable television channels they never watched, allowing them to bypass cable monopolies and pay only for the shows they wanted. No longer would anyone have to buy a $99-a-month triple-play package when all they wanted was the History Channel.

headline.main: Don’t Look Now, but the Great Unbundling Has Spun Into Reverse

docs.abstract: The company is putting its stamp on the city with an expanding array of unconventional experiments in bricks-and-mortar sales.
docs.snippet: The company is putting its stamp on the city with an expanding array of unconventional experiments in bricks-and-mortar sales.
docs.lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — On a busy stretch of road in this city’s Ballard neighborhood, a curious new grocery store is taking shape — and so begins another effort by Amazon to use the residents of its hometown as guinea pigs.

headline.main: Amazon’s Living Lab: Reimagining Retail on Seattle Streets

docs.abstract: Netflix may be the most popular movie and TV streaming service, but Hulu, Vudu and more also offer pleasures.
docs.snippet: Netflix may be the most popular movie and TV streaming service, but Hulu, Vudu and more also offer pleasures.
docs.lead_paragraph: There’s a reason people say — jokingly or not — “Netflix and chill” and not “Amazon Video and chill” or “Hulu and chill” or “Vudu and chill.”

headline.main: ‘Netflix and Chill’? Sure. But There Are Others, Too.
